{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":360,"text":"It's six o'clock in the morning,"},{"time":2600,"text":"pitch black outside."},{"time":4640,"text":"My 14-year-old son\nis fast asleep in his bed,"},{"time":7880,"text":"sleeping the reckless,\ndeep sleep of a teenager."},{"time":12000,"text":"I flip on the light and physically\nshake the poor boy awake,"},{"time":16000,"text":"because I know that,\nlike ripping off a Band-Aid,"},{"time":18640,"text":"it's better to get it over with quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22280,"text":"I have a friend who yells \"Fire!\"\njust to rouse her sleeping teen."},{"time":27040,"text":"And another who got so fed up"},{"time":29040,"text":"that she had to dump cold water\non her son's head"},{"time":31920,"text":"just to get him out of bed."},{"time":34600,"text":"Sound brutal ..."},{"time":36360,"text":"but perhaps familiar?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39600,"text":"Every morning I ask myself,"},{"time":42480,"text":"\"How can I --"},{"time":44080,"text":"knowing what I know"},{"time":45840,"text":"and doing what I do for a living --"},{"time":48280,"text":"be doing this to my own son?\""},{"time":51040,"text":"You see,"},{"time":52360,"text":"I'm a sleep researcher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56280,"text":"So I know far too much about sleep"},{"time":58120,"text":"and the consequences of sleep loss."},{"time":60840,"text":"I know that I'm depriving my son\nof the sleep he desperately needs"},{"time":64959,"text":"as a rapidly growing teenager."},{"time":67360,"text":"I also know that by waking him up"},{"time":69640,"text":"hours before his natural\nbiological clock tells him he's ready,"},{"time":74320,"text":"I'm literally robbing him\nof his dreams --"},{"time":77400,"text":"the type of sleep most associated\nwith learning, memory consolidation"},{"time":83200,"text":"and emotional processing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85760,"text":"But it's not just my kid\nthat's being deprived of sleep."},{"time":89760,"text":"Sleep deprivation among\nAmerican teenagers is an epidemic."},{"time":94360,"text":"Only about one in 10 gets\nthe eight to 10 hours of sleep per night"},{"time":98880,"text":"recommended by sleep scientists\nand pediatricians."},{"time":103280,"text":"Now, if you're thinking to yourself,"},{"time":105040,"text":"\"Phew, we're doing good,\nmy kid's getting eight hours,\""},{"time":108320,"text":"remember,"},{"time":109560,"text":"eight hours is\nthe minimum recommendation."},{"time":113080,"text":"You're barely passing."},{"time":115160,"text":"Eight hours is kind of like\ngetting a C on your report card."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118960,"text":"There are many factors\ncontributing to this epidemic,"},{"time":122600,"text":"but a major factor preventing teens\nfrom getting the sleep they need"},{"time":127160,"text":"is actually a matter of public policy."},{"time":130160,"text":"Not hormones, social lives or Snapchat."},{"time":135520,"text":"Across the country,"},{"time":136800,"text":"many schools are starting\naround 7:30am or earlier,"},{"time":141680,"text":"despite the fact that major\nmedical organizations recommend"},{"time":145800,"text":"that middle and high school\nstart no earlier than 8:30am."},{"time":151240,"text":"These early start policies\nhave a direct effect on how much --"},{"time":155400,"text":"or really how little sleep\nAmerican teenagers are getting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160520,"text":"They're also pitting\nteenagers and their parents"},{"time":164440,"text":"in a fundamentally unwinnable fight\nagainst their own bodies."},{"time":169360,"text":"Around the time of puberty,"},{"time":171200,"text":"teenagers experience a delay\nin their biological clock,"},{"time":174960,"text":"which determines when we feel most awake\nand when we feel most sleepy."},{"time":179520,"text":"This is driven in part by a shift\nin the release of the hormone melatonin."},{"time":184080,"text":"Teenagers' bodies wait to start releasing\nmelatonin until around 11pm,"},{"time":189640,"text":"which is two hours later than what\nwe see in adults or younger children."},{"time":195840,"text":"This means that waking a teenager up\nat 6am is the biological equivalent"},{"time":201880,"text":"of waking an adult up at 4am."},{"time":205760,"text":"On the unfortunate days\nwhen I have to wake up at 4am,"},{"time":209760,"text":"I'm a zombie."},{"time":211120,"text":"Functionally useless."},{"time":212880,"text":"I can't think straight,"},{"time":214520,"text":"I'm irritable,"},{"time":216040,"text":"and I probably shouldn't be driving a car."},{"time":219680,"text":"But this is how many American\nteenagers feel every single school day."},{"time":224280,"text":"In fact, many of the, shall we say,"},{"time":227320,"text":"unpleasant characteristics\nthat we chalk up to being a teenager --"},{"time":231680,"text":"moodiness, irritability,\nlaziness, depression --"},{"time":235120,"text":"could be a product\nof chronic sleep deprivation."},{"time":239080,"text":"For many teens\nbattling chronic sleep loss,"},{"time":241840,"text":"their go-to strategy to compensate\nis consuming large quantities of caffeine"},{"time":247360,"text":"in the form of venti frappuccinos,"},{"time":249560,"text":"or energy drinks and shots."},{"time":252080,"text":"So essentially,"},{"time":253320,"text":"we've got an entire population\nof tired but wired youth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261600,"text":"Advocates of sleep-friendly\nstart times know"},{"time":265240,"text":"that adolescence is a period\nof dramatic brain development,"},{"time":268800,"text":"particularly in the parts of the brain"},{"time":270880,"text":"that are responsible for those\nhigher order thinking processes,"},{"time":274440,"text":"including reasoning, problem-solving\nand good judgment."},{"time":279320,"text":"In other words, the very type\nof brain activity that's responsible"},{"time":282480,"text":"for reining in those impulsive\nand often risky behaviors"},{"time":287080,"text":"that are so characteristic of adolescence"},{"time":290040,"text":"and that are so terrifying\nto us parents of teenagers."},{"time":294600,"text":"They know that like the rest of us,"},{"time":296520,"text":"when teenagers don't\nget the sleep they need,"},{"time":298960,"text":"their brains, their bodies\nand behaviors suffer"},{"time":302120,"text":"with both immediate and lasting effects."},{"time":305280,"text":"They can't concentrate,"},{"time":307120,"text":"their attention plummets"},{"time":309040,"text":"and many will even show\nbehavioral signs that mimic ADHD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314320,"text":"But the consequences of teen sleep loss\ngo well beyond the classroom,"},{"time":318760,"text":"sadly contributing to many\nof the mental health problems"},{"time":322400,"text":"that skyrocket during adolescence,"},{"time":325120,"text":"including substance use,"},{"time":326960,"text":"depression and suicide."},{"time":330400,"text":"In our work with teens\nfrom LA Unified School District,"},{"time":333600,"text":"we found that teens with sleep problems"},{"time":335840,"text":"were 55 percent more likely\nto have used alcohol in the past month."},{"time":341080,"text":"In another study with over\n30,000 high school students,"},{"time":345000,"text":"they found that\nfor each hour of lost sleep,"},{"time":348600,"text":"there was a 38 percent increase\nin feeling sad or hopeless,"},{"time":353400,"text":"and a 58 percent increase\nin teen suicide attempts."},{"time":358600,"text":"And if that's not enough,"},{"time":360880,"text":"teens who skip out on sleep\nare at increased risk"},{"time":363440,"text":"for a host of physical health problems\nthat plague our country,"},{"time":367520,"text":"including obesity,\nheart disease and diabetes."},{"time":372760,"text":"Then there's the risk\nof putting a sleep-deprived teen,"},{"time":375680,"text":"with a newly minted driver's license,"},{"time":378240,"text":"behind the wheel."},{"time":380160,"text":"Studies have shown that getting five hours\nor less of sleep per night"},{"time":384680,"text":"is the equivalent of driving with a blood\nalcohol content above the legal limit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396200,"text":"Advocates of sleep-friendly start times,"},{"time":398720,"text":"and researchers in this area,"},{"time":400800,"text":"have produced tremendous science"},{"time":403000,"text":"showing the tremendous benefits\nof later start times."},{"time":406920,"text":"The findings are unequivocal,"},{"time":409240,"text":"and as a sleep scientist,"},{"time":410960,"text":"I rarely get to speak\nwith that kind of certainty."},{"time":415160,"text":"Teens from districts\nwith later start times get more sleep."},{"time":419000,"text":"To the naysayers who may think\nthat if schools start later,"},{"time":422520,"text":"teens will just stay up later,"},{"time":424920,"text":"the truth is,"},{"time":426200,"text":"their bedtimes stay the same,"},{"time":428160,"text":"but their wake-up times get extended,"},{"time":430440,"text":"resulting in more sleep."},{"time":433360,"text":"They're more likely to show up for school;"},{"time":435760,"text":"school absences dropped\nby 25 percent in one district."},{"time":439680,"text":"And they're less likely to drop out."},{"time":442280,"text":"Not surprisingly,\nthey do better academically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445800,"text":"So this has real implications\nfor reducing the achievement gap."},{"time":450560,"text":"Standardized test scores\nin math and reading"},{"time":453280,"text":"go up by two to three percentage points."},{"time":456320,"text":"That's as powerful as reducing class sizes\nby one-third fewer students,"},{"time":461920,"text":"or replacing a so-so teacher\nin the classroom"},{"time":465120,"text":"with a truly outstanding one."},{"time":468440,"text":"Their mental and physical health improves,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and even their families are happier."},{"time":473360,"text":"I mean, who wouldn't enjoy a little\nmore pleasantness from our teens,"},{"time":478200,"text":"and a little less crankiness?"},{"time":481040,"text":"Even their communities are safer"},{"time":482920,"text":"because car crash rates go down --"},{"time":485480,"text":"a 70 percent reduction in one district."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489400,"text":"Given these tremendous benefits,"},{"time":491840,"text":"you might think,"},{"time":493200,"text":"well, this is a no-brainer, right?"},{"time":495920,"text":"So why have we as a society\nfailed to heed this call?"},{"time":501680,"text":"Often the argument against later\nstart times goes something like this:"},{"time":506000,"text":"\"Why should we delay\nstart times for teenagers?"},{"time":508320,"text":"We need to toughen them up\nso they're ready for the real world!\""},{"time":512200,"text":"But that's like saying\nto the parent of a two-year-old,"},{"time":515120,"text":"\"Don't let Johnny nap,"},{"time":516640,"text":"or he won't be ready for kindergarten.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521880,"text":"Delaying start times also presents\nmany logistical challenges."},{"time":525800,"text":"Not just for students and their families,"},{"time":528200,"text":"but for communities as a whole."},{"time":530600,"text":"Updating bus routes,"},{"time":532200,"text":"increased transportation costs,"},{"time":534280,"text":"impact on sports,"},{"time":535840,"text":"care before or after school."},{"time":538280,"text":"These are the same concerns\nthat come up in district after district,"},{"time":542880,"text":"time and again around the country"},{"time":544880,"text":"as school start times are debated."},{"time":547960,"text":"And they're legitimate concerns,"},{"time":550640,"text":"but these are problems\nwe have to work through."},{"time":554120,"text":"They are not valid excuses"},{"time":556400,"text":"for failing to do the right thing\nfor our children,"},{"time":559920,"text":"which is to start middle and high schools\nno earlier than 8:30am."},{"time":565760,"text":"And in districts around the country,"},{"time":567680,"text":"big and small,\nwho have made this change,"},{"time":570320,"text":"they found that these fears\nare often unfounded"},{"time":574120,"text":"and far outweighed by the tremendous\nbenefits for student health"},{"time":578560,"text":"and performance,"},{"time":580240,"text":"and our collective public safety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584160,"text":"So tomorrow morning,"},{"time":585960,"text":"when coincidentally we get\nto set our clocks back by an hour"},{"time":591760,"text":"and you get that delicious\nextra hour of sleep,"},{"time":597280,"text":"and the day seems a little longer,"},{"time":600080,"text":"and a little more full of hope,"},{"time":602760,"text":"think about the tremendous power of sleep."},{"time":607520,"text":"And think about what a gift it would be"},{"time":610120,"text":"for our children to be able\nto wake up naturally,"},{"time":614160,"text":"in harmony with their own biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617400,"text":"Thank you,"},{"time":618680,"text":"and pleasant dreams."}]}]}